<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-01-09T13:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-01-09T13:40:00-05:00" n="68" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.51/2254: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Herod</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-09T14:00:00-04:40"><hi rend="italic">January 9,
                                        1922—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January 10—9:45
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>3. Your 1, January 7, 2 p.m. My action was to give [Military Governor] as
                            instructed your 27, December 21, 1 p.m. I gave Military Governor copy of
                            paraphrase of same made for Legation files. Your instructions number
                            429, December 23rd has not been received yet. The Dominican Government
                            is still unable to sell the certificates here.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Herod</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>